@startuml
title Where Frameworks End and Architecture Begins

' ===============================
' Shared Style
' ===============================
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Inter
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

top to bottom direction

skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 8
  BorderColor #1F2937
  FontColor #111827
}

skinparam arrow {
  Color #374151
  Thickness 1.5
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F9FAFB
  BorderColor #9CA3AF
  FontColor #374151
}

' ===============================
' Zones
' ===============================

rectangle #E5E7EB "Framework-Handled Concerns\n\n\
- Security (authn / authz)\n\
- Routing & dispatch\n\
- Schema & structural validation\n\
- Serialization & error mapping" as FW

rectangle #DBEAFE "Architectural Decision Zone\n\n\
- Business validation rules\n\
- Deterministic derivations\n\
- Persistence decisions\n\
- Responsibility boundaries" as ADZ

FW --> ADZ : responsibility handoff

note top of ADZ
Architecture begins where frameworks stop
enforcing boundaries.
end note

@enduml
